BSnes emulates the Super Game Boy completely, including sounds made by the SNES rather than just sounds made by the gameboy.  But it's slow, it doesn't even reach full speed on a 2GHz Core 2 Duo machine.<br />The currently distributed version of Bsnes called Higan doesn't seem to support the Super Game Boy though.  Or maybe it does, but doesn't seem to have any way to load super game boy games.  I got it to work with version 0.77, when loading Super Game Boy roms was still easy (provide a .GB file and the Super Game Boy .SFC file, rather than anything more complicated)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Mon Apr 01, 2013 1:23 pm</p><hr />
